com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface Topology

All Superinterfaces:
DeployModelObject
public interface Topology
extends DeployModelObject

A representation of the model object 'Topology'. A container of Unit instances expressing a deployment topology.

In the first release of the Topology Definition Model (TDM) a topology wholly contains all the links between its Unit instances. Future releases will support cross-topology linking.

The following features are supported:

  • Imports
  • Configuration Contract Group
  • Configuration Contract
  • Decorator Semantic
  • Namespace

See Also:

findHosts

Unit[] findHosts(Unit unit)
This API will return a array of Unit instances which host the passed unit.

For each element in the returned array there will be a HostingLink which has the passed unit as the hosted target.

This method will not return null.

Parameters:
unit - - The Unit which is being hosted.
Returns:
Unit[] of the hosts for the passed unit.

findMemberOf

Unit[] findMemberOf(Unit unit)
This API will return a array of Unit instances which consider the passed unit a member of their relationships.

For each element in the returned array there will be a MemberLink which has the passed unit as the member target.

This method will not return null.

Parameters:
unit - - The Unit which might be a member of some other Unit.
Returns:
Unit[] of the member link owner for the passed unit.

Queries getImports() to find a matching Import.

Parameters:

addTopologyListener

void addTopologyListener(Adapter listener,
                         java.lang.Object feature)
Add a listener that will get notifications for changes based on the registered feature. You must call removeTopologyListener(Adapter, Object) when you no longer want to receive notifications for this feature. Be sure to use the same feature that was used to add the listener.

Parameters:
listener - An Adapter that will listen to changes.
feature - An Object that you want to be notified of changes. Typically this is an EStructuralFeature.
See Also:
removeTopologyListener(Adapter, Object)

removeTopologyListener

void removeTopologyListener(Adapter listener,
                            java.lang.Object feature)
Remove a listener that is registered to receive topology wide changes based on a feature. Be sure to call removeTopologyListener(Adapter, Object) when listening is no longer required.

Parameters:
listener - An Adapter that will listen to changes.
feature - An Object that you want to stop being notified of changes. Typically this is an EStructuralFeature.
See Also:
removeTopologyListener(Adapter, Object)
